label: AB_tP4_129_c_c-001
title: $\gamma$-CuTi ($B11$) Structure
comments: When $c=2a$, $z_{1}=1/8$, and $z_{2}=5/8$, the atoms are on the sites of \href{current_web_home_dir/A_cI2_229_a-001}{a body-centered cubic lattice}. If, on the other hand, $c=2\sqrt{2a}$, with the same $z_{i}$, the atoms are on the site of \href{current_web_home_dir/A_cF4_225_a-001}{a face-centered cubic lattice}. This is the phase that (Lu, 1991) refer to as ``Z2''.
